<concept id="concept-9276" xml:lang="en-us" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Canvas automation</title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">This article demonstrates how <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> helps users to automate Canvas applications' test cases.</shortdesc><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><author translate="no" type="creator" class="- topic/author ">Dong Nguyen &lt;dong.nguyen@katalon.com&gt;</author><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><keywords class="- topic/keywords "/></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p ">A canvas is a rectangular area on an HTML page, and it is specified with the elements in HTML 5. All  objects inside the canvas can not be accessible via DOM (by Xpath, CSS, or Property). Because of the limited access to DOM, users have to find the coordinates for  objects before performing the actions.</p><section class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Use case</title><p class="- topic/p ">We have two different application which we have used for our sample project</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="https://www.online-calculator.com//html5/simple/index.php?v=10" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Online calculator</xref>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="https://kitchen.applitools.com/ingredients/canvas" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Kitchen application</xref>.</p></li></ul></section><section class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Test steps</title><p class="- topic/p "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">Perform calculations (1+8=9) on the calculator.</li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the Web application with Canvas.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Capture the Canvas Object.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Find the Coordinates for the Targeted Object inside the Canvas.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform the action.</p></li></ul></p></section></conbody></concept>